git clone https://github.com/username/repo_name local_folder
git fetch (not needed if cloned for the first time - needed later to pull other changes in)
git merge
git pull
git pull --rebase*
git stash

If the username prompt is annoying
git config -l # Find out the existing URL

git config remote.origin.url https://username@github.com/repo_username/project_name.git # Supply the username, only the password will be prompted for 

Better way may be to configure using SSH keys
